<p>Thank you for visiting californiawildfireclaim.org (referred to as the “Website” or “Site”). This Privacy Policy is intended to inform you about the types of information we collect when you use our Website and the associated services (“Services”), including applications, widgets, and email notifications. The term “californiawildfireclaim,” “Email Agency,” “we,” “our,” or “us” refers to californiawildfireclaim.org. We may update this Privacy Policy periodically, so please review this page regularly to stay informed of any changes.</p>
<p><strong>Intended Audience:</strong><br>This Website and the Services are designed for U.S. residents only.</p>
<p><strong>Information We Collect and How We Use It</strong></p>
<p>We assist consumers in finding insurance, discounted health plans, and other products by connecting them with relevant insurance companies, agents, discount program representatives, and vendors (“Service Providers”). We collect personally identifiable information (PII) that can identify you as an individual when you voluntarily provide this information, such as when you submit it through the Website. This information may include, but is not limited to, your first and last name, home address, telephone number, email address, date of birth, gender, income, and driver’s license information. Additionally, we may collect details about your driving history, the type of vehicle you drive, your home ownership history, and certain health-related information.</p>
<p>We use your PII for various lawful purposes, including:</p>
<p>– Delivering our products and services to you, including matching you with Service Providers.<br>– Displaying customized content and advertising.<br>– Conducting research and analysis to improve our services.<br>– Ensuring the proper functioning of the Website.<br>– Developing new services and features.<br>– Alerting you to product updates, special offers, and other new services.<br>– Responding to your requests for information.<br>– Sending newsletters and other communications.<br>– Providing quotes from Service Providers, who may contact you using the information you provide.<br>– Collecting additional information as needed.</p>
<p>We may also automatically gather certain information when you visit the Website, such as your IP address, browser type, internet service provider (ISP), referring/exit pages, operating system, date and time of visit, internet tags, device type, clickstream data, and other activities on the Website. This information may be combined with other data we collect about you to improve the services we offer, enhance marketing efforts, analyze trends, and improve Website functionality. We, along with our marketing partners, affiliates, and service providers, use technologies like cookies, beacons, tags, and scripts to collect this data. You can set your browser to reject cookies, but doing so may limit your ability to use certain features of the Website.</p>
<p><strong>Sharing of Personal Information</strong></p>
<p><strong>With Service Providers:</strong> When you provide PII to us, we may share it with Service Providers to provide you with the quotes you request and to allow them to contact you for informational, advertising, and marketing purposes. Service Providers and other third parties may contact you by email, telephone, text message, postal mail, or other means and may share your information with additional third parties without restriction.</p>
<p><strong>– Corporate Affiliates:</strong>&nbsp;We may share the information collected on the Website with our subsidiaries, corporate affiliates, and related companies.</p>
<p><strong>– Vendors and Suppliers: </strong>We may share your information with vendors and service providers for purposes such as verifying data and providing services like phone number verification and email distribution.</p>
<p><strong>– Legal Rights and Obligations:</strong>&nbsp;We may disclose PII as required by law or in response to lawful requests by public authorities. This includes law enforcement requests, compliance with legal processes, and protecting our legal rights, as well as the rights of others.</p>
<p><strong>– As Required by Law: </strong>We reserve the right to disclose your PII as necessary to protect our rights or comply with legal or judicial proceedings.</p>
<p><strong>– Business Transfers:</strong>&nbsp;In the event of bankruptcy, merger, or sale of assets, your information may be transferred as an asset of the Company.</p>
<p><strong>– Promotions and Programs:</strong>&nbsp;From time to time, you may have the opportunity to participate in promotions or programs offered by us or with third parties. Participation may require you to provide additional PII, and the use and sharing of that information will be governed by the rules or agreements specific to that promotion or program.</p>
<p><strong>Consent to Marketing Communications</strong></p>
<p>By providing your telephone number on the Website, you consent to receive informational and marketing messages and telephone calls from us and our Service Providers. These communications may include automated calls, text messages, SMS, MMS, picture messages, live and prerecorded calls, and more, even if your phone number is on a Do Not Call list. Consent is not required to purchase goods or services, and message &amp; data rates may apply. You can revoke your consent at any time by contacting us.</p>
<p><strong>Third-Party Websites and Services</strong></p>
<p>Please note that third-party websites and services, including those you connect with through our Website, may collect PII. This Privacy Policy does not cover the information practices of those third-party sites or services, and we are not responsible for their content or activities. Additionally, certain PII may be made available to third parties using our Application Programming Interface (API). The collection and use of data by these third parties are subject to their privacy policies.</p>
